svg.text: McCzarny recently pushed multiple updates to
the flexible-log-analyzer and upload-image
repositories. In flexible-log-analyzer, he
introduced performance logging with a new
PerformanceLogger class and a configurable
setting to track various operations. He also
enhanced log matchers by adding an enabled
field, allowing users to easily toggle them on
or off. Further improvements include
refactoring the logging extension to
incorporate an issue counter, visible as a
badge on the tree view, and implementing
caching for file path lookups to boost
clickable link performance with a new
fileLinkCacheSize setting. Additionally, he
updated several development dependencies, such
as @types/node,
@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin, and eslint,
to ensure stability and incorporate the latest
features. In the upload-image repository, a
significant update involved bumping the axios
dependency to version 1.12.0, bringing various
improvements and bug fixes. These activities
highlight his continuous effort in enhancing
functionality and maintaining project
dependencies.
